&lt;strong&gt;Syntax:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;(pointer_name)-&amp;gt;(variable_name)
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operation:&lt;/strong&gt; The -&amp;gt; operator in C or C++ gives the value held by variable_name to structure or union variable pointer_name.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Difference between Dot(.) and Arrow(-&amp;gt;) operator:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;. 和 -&amp;gt; 的区别&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Dot(.) operator is used to normally access members of a structure or union.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Arrow(-&amp;gt;) operator exists to access the members of the structure or the unions using pointers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
